Code to sum FTE and reshape data from wide to long format¶

I have a habit of making intermediate csv files just to make sure I don't get dataframes messed up. If you would like to have just one final csv, each time you make changes to your dataframe (copy of dataframe), you should re-assign it to a new variable name. Otherwise, you might not remember the changes to your dataframe and have problems later.

In [89]:
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

df_binary_0 = pd.read_csv('PA_head_value2_binary_med_drop_hy.csv')

Reshape data such that each value in the column, Specialty_keys, becomes a column heading.¶

In [115]:
#reshape data, from the wide format to the long format
#each unique value in the column Specialty_keys will become a column heading
upsideDown = df_binary5.pivot(index='IKN_addr', columns='Specialty_keys', values='Head_value')

Drop duplicates: because the merging is a 'one against multiple addresses' operation.¶

  • In the original file, each address is paired with multiple dentists and multiple specialties.
  • In the file produced after the FTE calculation, each address has only one entry for each specialty, because the head values have been summed.
  • When these two files merge by addresses so that the FTE file can regain the X, Y and other columns, you will get as many rows as the origianl file has. We are using the FTE file as our anchor, thus, we need to drop the duplicates.

Make sure that you perform this step when the Medicaid, CHIP and BOD-stand-alone parts are still separate! Once the three parts are combined into a final file, you shouldn't be dropping duplicates because there are providers who accept both Medicaid and CHIP and will appear twice.¶

In [127]:
df_combo.drop_duplicates(['IKN_addr']).to_csv('PA_specialty_sum.csv',index=False)
In [128]:
df_combo2a =pd.read_csv('PA_specialty_sum.csv')

Add the two hygienist columns and populate them with values derive from multiplying the general and pediatic columns by 2 (assuming each dentists has two hygienists).¶

In [133]:
#add the column for hygienists who work under dentists, assuming each dentist employs two hygienists
df_combo2['hygienist_for_general']=df_combo2['general'].apply(lambda x: x*2)
df_combo2['hygienist_for_pediatric']=df_combo2['pediatric'].apply(lambda x: x*2)
